cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with multi-robot systems and their behavior mixing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a real-time distributed algorithm for connectivity maintenance and control barrier functions for connectivity constraints and collision avoidance. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with multiple agents (robots) and their coordination. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the proposed algorithm is distributed and real-time. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is less likely but still relevant as the paper deals with maintaining connectivity within and across subgroups in a communication graph.
